testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Public harness APIs such as MojoRule, AbstractMojoTestCase, MavenProjectStub, and ArtifactStubFactory expose Maven core/model/plugin/artifact types that are provided by the harness build rather than reliably pulled by the scaffold.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven:maven-compat:3.2.5\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Several harness stubs and resolver helpers reference legacy Maven compatibility/artifact resolver classes.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"junit:junit:4.11\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"MojoRule and TestResources are JUnit 4 rules/watchers, and the harness documentation for this version demonstrates JUnit 4 usage.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Exercise the harness as a Maven-plugin testing library: create minimal in-test Mojo/project fixtures and cover MojoRule or AbstractMojoTestCase setup, MavenProjectStub/ArtifactStubFactory, MojoParameters, TestResources, and SilentLog. The test should initialize the harness container/rule or use the stub APIs directly rather than only instantiating classes.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The library is designed to test Maven plugins, so meaningful coverage may require small synthetic plugin descriptors or temporary POM/resources in the test.\",\n    \"JUnit 4 APIs are distinct from the scaffold's JUnit Jupiter test runner; use them as library objects/rules where useful, while keeping the generated test executable under the repository harness.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0aee02553c2f023e016a284cbaf478819493498de96db1f93e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 532, "output": 965, "cacheRead": 36864, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38361, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781025964053, "responseId": "resp_0aee02553c2f023e016a284cad532c8194b56c7141aff39619"}}
